Package main

Class Musial

java.lang.Object
main.Musial
public final class Musial
extends java.lang.Object
Main class of MUSIAL (MUlti Sample varIant AnaLysis), a tool to calculate SNV, gene, and whole genome alignments, together with other relevant statistics based on vcf files.
Since:
1.0
Version:
2.1
Author:
Alexander Seitz, Simon Hackl

    • parseCLIArguments

      private static CLIParameters parseCLIArguments​(java.lang.String[] args) throws MusialCLException, MusialIOException, MusialBioException, MusialIntegrityException
      Parses command line arguments by instantiating an object implementing the CLIParameters interface.

      The command line arguments specified by the user and accepted by the `main` method are passed and used to instantiate an object implementing the CLIParameters interface which is returned if all argument validation steps were successful. If any error arises during the parsing step the program exits.

      Parameters:
      args - Arguments parsed from the command line.
      Returns:
      An instance of the CLIParametersUpdateVDict class.
      Throws:
      MusialCLException - See documentation of CLIParametersUpdateVDict class.
      MusialIOException - See documentation of CLIParametersUpdateVDict class.
      MusialBioException - See documentation of CLIParametersUpdateVDict class.
      MusialIntegrityException - See documentation of CLIParametersUpdateVDict class.

    • runUpdateVDict

      private static void runUpdateVDict​(CLIParametersUpdateVDict cliarguments) throws java.lang.InterruptedException, MusialIOException, MusialIntegrityException, MusialBioException, java.io.IOException
      Generates a new or updates an existing variants dictionary JSON file based on the specifications parsed from a variants dictionary specification JSON file.
      Parameters:
      cliarguments - CLIParametersUpdateVDict instance yielding parameter specification for the MUSIAL update variants dictionary module.
      Throws:
      java.lang.InterruptedException - Thrown if any Runnable implementing class instance is interrupted by the user.
      MusialIOException - Thrown if any input or output file is missing or unable to being generated (caused by any MUSIAL method).
      java.io.IOException - Thrown if any input or output file is missing or unable to being generated (caused by any native Java method).
      MusialIntegrityException - Thrown if any method fails wrt. internal logic, i.e. assignment of proteins to genomes.
      MusialBioException - Thrown if any method fails wrt. biological context, i.e. parsing of unknown symbols.
